// RingBuffer
// Fixed-capacity circular buffer that stores terminal output lines for reconnect replay.
// Oldest lines are evicted when the buffer is full.

Holds up to maxLines lines (default 10,000). Partial lines — chunks that arrive without a
trailing newline — are appended to the previous entry rather than counted as a new line.
Only complete lines (ending with \n) count toward the line limit.

FUNCTION constructor(maxLines)                                          EXPORT
  Initialize an empty lines array with the given capacity limit (default 10,000).

---

FUNCTION write(data)                                                    EXPORT
  If data is empty, return immediately.
  Split data on newlines. For each complete segment (all but the last):
    Append it as a new line. IF the buffer now exceeds maxLines, evict the oldest.
  For the trailing segment (which may be empty or a partial line with no newline):
    IF it is non-empty:
      IF the last stored entry is itself a partial line (no trailing \n), append to it.
      ELSE push it as a new partial entry, evicting the oldest if over capacity.

---

FUNCTION getContents() -> string                                        EXPORT
  Return all buffered entries joined into a single string, preserving ANSI codes.

---

FUNCTION clear()                                                        EXPORT
  Reset the buffer to empty.

---

FUNCTION lineCount -> number                                            EXPORT
  Return the count of entries that end with \n (complete lines only; partials excluded).
